The paper proposes a deep learning method for nonnegative matrix factorization (NMF) to learn hierarchical features of complex data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on clustering analysis, it is less likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer graphics (cs.GR) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
